2.1.3 Making function definitions more concise by using expression bodies
	- If a function is written with its body in curly braces
		-> function has a "block body"

	- If a function returns an expression directly
		-> function has an "expression body"

	* omitting the return type is allowed only for functions with an expression body.
		ex)
			================================================================================================================
			// No return type but the compiler knows. (Type inference)
			fun max(a: Int, b: Int) = if(a>b) a else b 
			================================================================================================================
	
